[Avian influenza still rages on in the Americas. I had hoped that with some of our high temperatures in many parts of the USA and Canada, and some migration routes not being as active, this virus might be dying out. However, these postings clearly indicate this nemesis is still plaguing our domestic birds and other animals it spills over into.

Clearly, vigilance to protect your birds cannot be relaxed. Keep your birds inside, and practice biosecurity until it is automatic and always in place.

For the birds, and for those dealing with these tragedies, we hope this situation abates. - Mod.TG

